    "##### 12. Write a function using only list comprehensions, no loops, to compute standard deviation. Using this function, calculate the standard deviation of each numeric column in both data sets. Add these to a list called `sd`.\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\sigma = \\sqrt{\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i - \\mu)^2}$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 36,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def std_dev(sample):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Computes standard deviation using list comprehensions.\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    std = np.sqrt(np.sum([((i - np.nanmean(sample))**2) for i in sample]) / len(sample))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return std"
   ]
  },

    "def confidencer(sample, sd=0.95):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Take in sample and sig. level, then return CI\n",
    "    sample = dataset\n",
    "    sd = significance level, default 95%.\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    zscore = stats.norm.ppf(1-(1-sd)/2) \n",
    "    \n",
    "    low_ci = sample.mean() - zscore*sample.sem()\n",
    "\n",
    "    high_ci = sample.mean() + zscore*sample.sem()\n",
    "    \n",
    "#     interval = (low_ci, high_ci)\n",
    "    print((low_ci, high_ci))\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(\"{0:.0f}% of similar sample means will fall between the range above.\".format(sd*100))\n",
    "    \n",
    "#     return (low_ci, high_ci)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 86,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [

      "95% of similar sample means will fall between the range above.\n"
     ]
    }
